external_knowledge:
- In seismology, a magnitude of 6.0 or higher is often considered significant and can cause substantial damage or impact; 
- The Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI) scale is used to measure the intensity of shaking produced by an earthquake; 
- Spectral accelerations (sa_0_3, sa_1_0, sa_3_0) are important in assessing the potential impact of an earthquake on structures; 
- Peak Ground Acceleration (pga) and Peak Ground Velocity (pgv) are key indicators of the severity of the ground shaking.

